Name: EpmCaSI1ErrSig
Title: Engine speed sensing: DFC for camshaft signal diagnosis - disturbed signal
Fid Name:
1) FId_CoDsplCtl_Limp
2) FId_ComNEngNPL
3) FId_EpmCaSAdapCaSI1
4) FId_EpmCaSErrCaSI1
5) FId_EpmCaSSpdPlausI1
6) FId_DSR93
Fid Description:
1) FId / Limp home mode activated
2) Fid / Error in reception of CAN message ComNEngNPL
3) FId / Camshaft position adaption (learning of real position to the theoretical one) inhibited
4) FId / Camshaft 1 sensor diagnosis inhibited
5) Fid / Inhibits use of camshaft speed of intake camshaft bank 1 to invalid
6) Fid sets recovery curve evREF_CURVE_LTD1
System Reaction:
If problem is detected at engine start, a redundant synchronisation of the angular system is performed using only the crankshaft increment signal and test injections to determine engine phase, if procedure fails the injection is aborted and the system waits for a restart.

See also FIDs list.

Fid Name:
1) FId_TECUFrzVal0
2) FId_TECUPhysRng0
3) FId_TECURplVal0
Fid Description:
1) FId / Freeze ECU temperature value if preliminary failure is detected
2) FId / Inhibits physical range check of ECU0 temperature
3) FId / Replace ECU temperature with default value if failure is vaildated
System Reaction:
Temperature is frozen at last valid value on preliminary failure and jumps to fixed replacement value 39.96C if failure is validated.
